<h2>Why you're doing this</h2>

<p>Over the next nine months you'll evaluate hundreds of sources — papers, news, government reports, AI outputs, your classmates' arguments. The Source Dossier is the first time you do that work for a grade. It's intentionally small: pick one contested scientific topic, find three sources (including at least one AI source), OPVL each, and defend your evaluation in 5 minutes.</p>

<p>Why "contested"? Because uncontested topics don't force you to actually evaluate sources — you just agree with whichever one you read. Contested topics force you to notice that sources disagree, ask why, and figure out which source is good for what.</p>

